question.title: IntelliJ won't expand collapsed rows
question.body:
Anytime I create the studentMenu() or profMenu() shown in the screenshot, IntelliJ collapses the rows in that method and will not let me expand them (both via Expand button in row number column or right click Foldering > Expand or Expand All).

I use these methods in my main() method, but this issue occurs even if I comment them out before and after creating these methods.

This is for a homework assignment.

Things I've tried:

  • Restarting IntelliJ multiple times
  • Committing changes in class where methods are created
  • Copying similar method and changing name
  • Writing new method from scratch
  • Changing access modifiers
  • Adding/removing static
  • Changing return type
  • Creating method with desired code
  • Creating method with no code
  • Removed all default Java auto-collapse boxes under Code Foldering setting
  • Created methods in different places within class (i.e. specific row numbers aren't the issue)

None of these attempts resolved the issues.
